pipeline-config
Pipeline Configuration
Tool
GitHub Actions
Trigger
Runs automatically on every push to the main branch.
How it works
1. Developer pushes code to GitHub.
2. GitHub Actions checks out the repo.
3. Using appleboy/ssh-action , it SSHs into the EC2 instance with credentials stored as GitHub Secrets (never
hardcoded).
4. On the EC2 instance, it pulls the latest code, copies index.html into Nginx’s web root, and reloads Nginx.
5. Zero manual deployment steps required after the initial setup.
Secrets used (GitHub → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions)
Secret Value
EC2_HOST EC2 public IPv4 address
EC2_USERNAME ubuntu
EC2_SSH_KEY Full private key contents ( .pem file)
Secrets are used specifically so no credentials ever appear in the repo or the workflow file itself.
Workflow file — .github/workflows/deploy.yml
name: Deploy to EC2
on:
push:
branches:
- main
jobs:
deploy:
runs-on: ubuntu-latest
steps:
# Step 1: Download the code
- name: Checkout code
uses: actions/checkout@v3
# Step 2: Deploy to EC2 via SSH
- name: Deploy to EC2
uses: appleboy/ssh-action@master
with:
host: ${{ secrets.EC2_HOST }}
username: ${{ secrets.EC2_USERNAME }}
key: ${{ secrets.EC2_SSH_KEY }}
script: |
# Pull latest code from GitHub
cd /tmp
rm -rf devops-aws-assignment
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME/devops-aws-assignment.git
Replace YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME with your actual GitHub username before committing.
Verification
GitHub → Actions tab shows the workflow run.
Green tick = successful deploy. Yellow circle = in progress. Red X = failed (click the run → “deploy” step for the
error log).
Confirm the change is live by refreshing http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>/ after the run completes.
Common failure and fix
SSH connection refused — usually means port 22 isn’t reachable from GitHub’s runner IP range. - Temporarily open
port 22 to 0.0.0.0/0 in the Security Group to confirm this is the cause, run the pipeline, then restrict it back to “My IP”
afterward. - Double-check the EC2_SSH_KEY secret contains the entire .pem file contents, including the -----
BEGIN...----- and -----END...----- lines.
# Copy new index.html to Nginx web folder
sudo cp devops-aws-assignment/index.html /var/www/html/index.html
sudo chown www-data:www-data /var/www/html/index.html
# Reload Nginx to serve new version
sudo systemctl reload nginx
echo "Deployment successful"
